{"questionId":"17505","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>Consider the lines <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"{L_1}\">\n  <mrow>\n    <msub>\n      <mi>L</mi>\n      <mn>1</mn>\n    </msub>\n  </mrow>\n</math></span> and <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"{L_2}\">\n  <mrow>\n    <msub>\n      <mi>L</mi>\n      <mn>2</mn>\n    </msub>\n  </mrow>\n</math></span> with respective equations</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center;\"><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"{L_1}\\,{\\text{:}}\\,y =&nbsp; - \\frac{2}{3}x + 9\">\n  <mrow>\n    <msub>\n      <mi>L</mi>\n      <mn>1</mn>\n    </msub>\n  </mrow>\n  <mspace width=\"thinmathspace\"></mspace>\n  <mrow>\n    <mtext>:</mtext>\n  </mrow>\n  <mspace width=\"thinmathspace\"></mspace>\n  <mi>y</mi>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mo>−</mo>\n  <mfrac>\n    <mn>2</mn>\n    <mn>3</mn>\n  </mfrac>\n  <mi>x</mi>\n  <mo>+</mo>\n  <mn>9</mn>\n</math></span>&nbsp; and&nbsp;&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"{L_2}{\\text{:}}\\,y = \\frac{2}{5}x - \\frac{{19}}{5}\">\n  <mrow>\n    <msub>\n      <mi>L</mi>\n      <mn>2</mn>\n    </msub>\n  </mrow>\n  <mrow>\n    <mtext>:</mtext>\n  </mrow>\n  <mspace width=\"thinmathspace\"></mspace>\n  <mi>y</mi>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mfrac>\n    <mn>2</mn>\n    <mn>5</mn>\n  </mfrac>\n  <mi>x</mi>\n  <mo>−</mo>\n  <mfrac>\n    <mrow>\n      <mn>19</mn>\n    </mrow>\n    <mn>5</mn>\n  </mfrac>\n</math></span>.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>A third line, <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"{L_3}\">\n  <mrow>\n    <msub>\n      <mi>L</mi>\n      <mn>3</mn>\n    </msub>\n  </mrow>\n</math></span>, has gradient&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\" - \\frac{3}{4}\">\n  <mo>−</mo>\n  <mfrac>\n    <mn>3</mn>\n    <mn>4</mn>\n  </mfrac>\n</math></span>.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>Write down a direction vector for <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"{L_3}\"> <mrow> <msub> <mi>L</mi> <mn>3</mn> </msub> </mrow> </math></span>.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"\\left( {\\begin{array}{*{20}{c}}  { - 4} \\\\   3  \\end{array}} \\right)\"> <mrow> <mo>(</mo> <mrow> <mtable columnspacing=\"1em\" rowspacing=\"4pt\"> <mtr> <mtd> <mrow> <mo>−</mo> <mn>4</mn> </mrow> </mtd> </mtr> <mtr> <mtd> <mn>3</mn> </mtd> </mtr> </mtable> </mrow> <mo>)</mo> </mrow> </math></span>&nbsp; (or any multiple of <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"\\left( {\\begin{array}{*{20}{c}} { - 4} \\\\&nbsp; 3&nbsp; \\end{array}} \\right)\"> <mrow> <mo>(</mo> <mrow> <mtable columnspacing=\"1em\" rowspacing=\"4pt\"> <mtr> <mtd> <mrow> <mo>−</mo> <mn>4</mn> </mrow> </mtd> </mtr> <mtr> <mtd> <mn>3</mn> </mtd> </mtr> </mtable> </mrow> <mo>)</mo> </mrow> </math></span>)&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>A1&nbsp; N1</strong></em></p>\n<p><em><strong>[1 mark]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"17505","referenceCode":"19N.2.SL.TZ0.S_2b","subjectId":"50-dp-mathematics-analysis-and-approaches","title":"Write down a direction vector for L 3 .","paper":"2","level":"SL","questionNumber":"b","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 1]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 2—Functions","Topic 3— Geometry and trigonometry","Topic 3— Geometry and trigonometry","AHL 3.12—Vector definitions","Topic 3— Geometry and trigonometry","AHL 3.14—Vector equation of line","Topic 2—Functions","SL 2.10—Solving equations graphically and analytically"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}